snippet.textDisplay: At 15:10, you were almost there by stating a fact, the new HEMI does not have HEMIspherical combustion chambers as the earlier engines but then you had to keep MOpar PARts happy by saying at 15:37 "It's still a freekin HEMI". From what I remember about the 5.7 (346 ci) cylinder head when it came out, they tried to make it a hemispherical, but it would not pass emissions. But advertisers know how to make money so they stuck their trademarked name on it and here we are today. I wish you would have shown some pictures of earlier Chrysler hemispherical heads to the now Fiat so called hemispherical heads so people can see the differences in the chambers. Don't forget about the banned from NASCAR from even being raced, the answer to the 426 HEMI, the Ford Cammer. This engine was put in a ’64 Galaxie and ran at the time the fastest lap at Daytona. https://www.streetmusclemag.com/tech-stories/engine/the-anatomy-of-the-427-sohc-fords-answer-to-the-hemi/
